                        SCROTAX II - Release Notes
                        ==========================

                               Version 2.01
                               ============

Scrotax v2.00 came out with two horrifying (and frustrating beyond belief)
bugs.  They were:

* That the game wouldn't run unless you had Amos Pro v2.00 library!!!  I
  can't believe this one!  Drove me mad when I realised!  If you got a
  SOFTWARE ERROR or NEEDS AMOS LIBRARY or something similar, then this
  should now be fixed!  I hope.

* If you selected SAVE from the main menu then it crashed (it's ok - AFTER
  saving - just bl**dy stupid one!)

ALSO - I didn't mean to upload it with my own personal high score table!
Whoops!  V2.00 high scores will work with v2.01 fine (and vice versa)


- Several other changes have been made as well!  Nothing hugely major, but
  the "realistic" gravity was a nice idea - thanks to Ben Wyatt - one which
  bizarrely passed me by (or was it a sub-conscious desire not to do
  something I didn't think I could!)

- See the Amigaguide for a list of ALL changes to Scrotax!

- V2.01 isn't much of an update, I admit that, but I needed to upload it
  quickly with the two major bugs above fixed and as I no longer had v2.00
  I had to just upload the most recent version.  I was planning to wait a
  while and release it with a few extra bits to it!  Ho hum... when I
  eventually come to v2.02 there will hopefully be a few extra new bits to
  it!


